Product Description

UGREEN High-Q USB C to Lightning Cable for PD Fast Charge and 480Mbps Data Sync [MFi-Certified]

Read more

3A Fast-Charging

- Delivers a high-speed charge up to 3A (max) with the USB-C PD charger, to charge an iPhone 12 from 0% to 50% in 30 mins.

One-for-More

- Use the C to Lightning cable with your USB-C PD Charger (including Apple 18W, 20W, 30W, 45W, 61W or 87W USB-C Power Adapter) to charge your iOS device.

Data Transfer

- It offers data to sync up to 480Mbps, transfer music, movie, files between iPhone and USB-C laptops in seconds.

Safe and Reliable

- UGREEN USB C to Lightning cable made from original Apple chips provides a secure and stable voltage.

Cable Length: 3FT/6FT/10FT (1M/2M/3M)

      MrMark
      1.0 out of 5 stars Stiff and ungainly
      Reviewed in the United States on September 2, 2020
      Size: 6FTVerified Purchase
      I guess I'm going to have to give up on UGREEN cables. I got one that I thought was good, but now I've gotten three in a row that are terrible. This particular cable is so stiff that it flips my iPhone over if I try to make the cable lie flat on my desk. It also tends to spin the phone around so that I can't read it. It's just a very bulky, stiff, and unhandy cable.

      The outside diameter is hard to measure because the cable is kind of lumpy, meaning that the OD varies depending on the exact point of measurement, but it's about 4.4 mm ( 0.173"). For comparison, the Apple cable that came with my iPhone is 2.9 mm (0.114") and a 1m Apple USB-C / Lightning cable is 3.4 mm (0.134"). This cable is a lot bulkier and the difference in flexibility is not insignificant.

      For anyone who associates thickness with goodness, maybe this cable will seem good, but in my mind, the lack of flexibility serves only to impose excessive strain on the connectors, both on the cable and also in the connected devices. There's more to durability and build quality than sheer size. Personally, I don't think this cable will prove to be all that durable, but even if it did, if it destroyed my chargers and my connected devices, it would be a lousy trade-off.

      Dump truck tires are bigger and more durable than grand touring tires, but which would be better for a road trip in a nice car? Speaking for myself, I'm going to return this cable and go for Apple's "GT"-like offering.

      Dan G.
      5.0 out of 5 stars Slightly better than Apples OEM USB-C to lightning cable.
      Reviewed in the United States on May 3, 2020
      Size: 3FTVerified Purchase
      I tested this cable versus Apples OEM USB-C lightning cable, using a USB-C test device measuring voltage and current. I was powering an Apple iPad 5th generation using Apples OEM 30-Watt USB-C wall charger.

      The voltage delivered to the tablet was exactly the same at 5.08 volts. The Apple cable delivered 2.58 amps to the tablet, while this UGreen cable delivered 2.61 amps. The difference is minuscule, slightly over 1%, so youd never notice it in reduced charging times.

      In addition, this cable is more durable than the Apple cable. I have had several over the years in which the insulator cracks near the plugs and shows the wires inside. This cable is braided, and will likely last longer than the Apple cables.

      This cable is a very good replacement for the OEM Apple USB-C to Lightning cable.
